<Author>jayrhizola
<Content>Friendly Hotel staff would have gone a long way The location is not ideal for someone looking to explore the city. It is too far away and considering the cost of transportation in Amsterdam, a hotel in the city is a better option.The staff are not very friendly and to me they seem to always wear sour faces, whcih was a surprise since everywhere else in Amsterdam, everyone I met were extremely friendly and helpful. A smile will go a long way to make hotel guests feel more comfortable.The staff and manageent were also dishonest. I was expecting a package from Hamburg and for two days I was following up with management if the package has arrived. All I got was a response that no package has arrived and I had to check out of the hotel without the package. Surprise, surprise...I later found out from the delivery company that the package was not accepted by the staff for some unknown reason. All along, someone made a mistake of refusing to accept the package on my behalf but they could not own up to the mistake and tell me what has happened. 
