<Author>AJArmstrong
<Content>Satisfactory I recently stayed here to attend a concert in Amsterdam and found it like the other reviews to be ok, nothing special. It is very convenient for the airport and not too far from a tram line which takes you into the city centre in about 20 mins. My complaint, like the others is that there is absolutely no justification to call this the city centre. A taxi back from the centre costs around EUR20. However the Leidseplein area where many of the best bars/clubs can be found, is much closer and only 10 mins by tram and about EUR11 by cab. The staff were pretty un motivated and could be found in a lounge behind reception smoking and chatting and certainly not making guests their first priority. They were fairly pleasant when you did find them, but some smiles and a bit more friendliness towards their customers wouldn't go amiss! There is also a pretty dire stench in the corridors and the bathrooms have a bit of a smell. Perhaps this is the drains? I think hotel management should look into it. Other than that a pretty average place, does the job if you're not too fussed about where you stay. 
