<Author>cdcdcd
<Content>Not as bad as the reviews suggest.... I booked this hotel, having read the reviews, because we had a car with us and the more central hotels did not have car parks - parking on the street in Amsterdam is expensive. The hotel was clean and comfortable with a seperate adjoining room for the children. It WAS too hot, as another reviewer mentioned. The trains going by are lous with the windows open, but we enjoyed watching them late at night from the high window! Breakfast was fine, although they pack away promptly at the end, so give yourself time. It IS about 15 minutes on the trams, and I wouldnt recommend travelling alone at night as the walk back is through an industrial estate and under a flyover. That said, Amsterdam is fairly safe for a major city, and we didnt intend to be out late with children. Metros run frequently. 
