<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>The Peckham of Amsterdam This hotel is MILES from Amsterdam (30 minutes on the Tram) and has no right to describe itself as anywhere near Central Station or any of the attractions.The hotel is clean and tidy enough, but this part of town is NOT somewhere you want to return to after a night on the tiles. It resides on an industrial estate surrounded by motorway fly-overs and building sites. The only safe way to return at the end of each day is to hire a taxi - and that's going to cost you 20 Euros each time.The staff were friendly enough but where mostly unobtainable. Whilst staying here I witnessed several complaints from customers and breakfast was frankly a shambles. We couldn't get into our room for two hours because the key\lock was broken and when we did there was an unpleasant smell coming from the toilet.When you take into account the taxi fares you're better off booking somewhere closer to the centre of Amsterdam. 
